\item \verb{cd ..} moves \emph{out} one level: it finds the directory that
contains the current directory, then makes that directory the
current directory.
\item \verb{cd /} switches the current directory to the outermost
directory, \code{/}.
}
\item \code{ls} means \emph{list}. It prints out all of the files and directories
immediately contained by the current directory:
\itemize{
\item \verb{123 abc} means that the current directory contains a file named
